The Textbook is one of the best modern algebra books in recent years. It sets the standard as the most current and comprehensive resource in modern algebra.

2. Stephen H. Friedberg, Arnold J. Insel & Lawrence E. Spence, Linear Algebra, 4Ed., Prentice Hall, 2003[Mathematical Approach]
3. Jimmie Gilbert and Linda Gilbert, Linear Algebra and Matrix Theory,2nd Ed., Thomson 2004 [Math Approach]
4. Kenneth Hoffman and Ray Kunze, Linear Algebra, Prentice-Hall, Englewood Cliffs, NJ,  2nd ed.,1971 ISBN 978-0-13-536797-1, [Mathematical Approach]
5. Serge Lang, Linear Algebra, Undergraduate Texts in Mathematics(3rd ed.), Springer, 2004, ISBN 978-0-387-96412-6
6. Steven J. Leon, Linear Algebra with Applications, 8th ed., Pearson Prentice-Hall, 2010[Numerical Version]
7. Seymour Lipschutz and  Marc Lipson,  Schaum's Outline of Theory and Problems of Linear Algebra,  5th Edition(Schaum's Outline Series), McGraw-Hill Companies, 2008, [Solved Problems Series]
8.Martin Moskowitz and Fotios Paliogiannis, Functions ofSeveral real variables, World Scientific, 2011
9. John Srdjan Petrovic, Advanced Calculus Theory and Practice, CRC Press, 2014
10. Edoardo Sernesi, Linear Algebra, Chapman & Hall, London, 1993[Geometric Approach]
11. Gilbert Strang, Introduction to Linear Algebra, 4th edition. Wellesley-Cambridge Press and SIAM , 2009
12. Treil, Sergei, Linear Algebra Done Wrong , Brown University, online (http://www.math.brown.edu/~treil/papers/LADW/LADW.html)
